Tradesy Recommendations Functional Test Read Me

This is the functional test suite for the recommendations api service.

Requirements:
1. You will need to have node the node package manager installed. If using homebrew, you run install by running "sudo brew install npm"
2. Run "npm install" in ~/Projects/tradesy-core/tradesy-service-recommendations/tests/Functional (package.json should be in here)
3. To run the test suite, run "npm test"
3a. To run a specific suite run "REC_URL=http://dev.services.trsy.io/recommendations mocha test" or "REC_URL=http://dev.services.trsy.io/recommendations mocha test {{location}}"

Run in PhpStorm:
1. Install "NodeJs" plugin in Preferences -> Plugins
2. Go to Run -> Edit Configurations... Select Defaults dropdown on left column. Select Mocha and add a new environment variable:
    REC_URL=http://dev.services.trsy.io/recommendations
3. Click apply.
4. You should be able to run tests by right clicking on a file or a test method.


